        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 2:46PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 246 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of Oasis, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oasis and Silver Zone Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
